"Place cheese in mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Add flour and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add milk, reserved grated cheese, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, 1 tsp salt and pepper then cook <b>7 min\/90°C\/speed 3<b>. Meanwhile, bring a large saucepan of water with 1 tsp salt added to the boil."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Cook spaghetti according to packet instructions, or until al dente. Drain well using a colander and transfer to a large bowl."},{"content":"Pour cheese sauce over cooked spaghetti and mix well to combine. Divide spaghetti between 4 serving plates,  drizzle over a little olive oil then sprinkle some pangrattato over each. Serve immediately with remaining pangrattato."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use cheese you may have leftover from a cheeseboard or dinner party. A combination of a creamy cheese such as brie, some sharp cheddar, and a strong blue works well.","Give leftover cheese a new lease of life with this simple yet flavourful pasta dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}